{# Free tier promise #}
<section class="mt-16 sm:mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl tracking-tight text-text-primary">The free tier promise</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base/7 text-text-secondary mx-auto">
      The core product—tracking your job applications—will always be free. Not "free with ads," not "free because I'm selling your data." <strong>FREE.</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base/7 text-text-secondary mx-auto">
      While cloud maintenance costs are unavoidable as the product scales, my goal is to continue providing value with the app's core functionality to as many users as possible. Please consider supporting this product with a donation to make this possible. 
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

{# Buy me a coffee #}
<section class="mt-16 sm:mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto text-center">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl tracking-tight text-text-primary">Support open source software!</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base text-text-secondary">If you found value in Trackur, or if you hated it and want to toss me a coin because you believe I'll starve in the streets without your kindness, please make a contribution to keep this open-source project afloat.</p>
    <a href="#" class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold border-theme rounded-theme text-text-primary hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-theme">
      <svg class="size-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21 8.25c0-2.485-2.099-4.5-4.688-4.5-1.935 0-3.597 1.126-4.312 2.733-.715-1.607-2.377-2.733-4.313-2.733C5.1 3.75 3 5.765 3 8.25c0 7.22 9 12 9 12s9-4.78 9-12Z"/></svg>
      Buy me a coffee
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

{# Paid features survey #}
<section class="mt-16 sm:mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <div class="p-8 border-theme rounded-theme-xl bg-bg-alt">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-caption tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Looking ahead</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary">Features that might cost money someday</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm/6 text-text-secondary">
        I'm exploring features that involve data storage and server costs—stuff like resume uploads, automated follow-up reminders, and email notifications. If these drive up maintenance costs, they may need a paid tier. If you'd find value in any of these, let me know.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# FAQ #}
<section class="mt-20 sm:mt-28 mb-8">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl tracking-tight text-text-primary text-center">Questions</h2>
    <div class="mt-10 space-y-0 divide-y divide-border-default">
      {% for item in pricing.faq %}
      <details class="group py-5">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-semibold text-text-primary">
          {{ item.question }}
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 text-text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm/6 text-text-secondary pr-8">{{ item.answer }}</p>
      </details>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
